# Context7 Integration Rules

## Library Versions for Prompts

Always use these exact versions when using Context7 in Cursor prompts:

```
react@19.2.0
react-dom@19.2.0
next@16.0.1
tailwindcss@4
typescript@5
@radix-ui/react-dialog@1.1.15
@radix-ui/react-dropdown-menu@2.1.16
@radix-ui/react-label@2.1.7
@radix-ui/react-select@2.2.6
@radix-ui/react-slot@1.2.3
@radix-ui/react-switch@1.2.6
@radix-ui/react-tabs@1.1.13
@radix-ui/react-tooltip@1.2.8
class-variance-authority@0.7.1
clsx@2.1.1
tailwind-merge@3.3.1
lucide-react@0.548.0
```

## Design System Rules

### Design Tokens
- ALWAYS use tokens from `app/globals.css`
- NEVER use hardcoded colors (#hex, rgb, hsl)
- Use Tailwind classes that map to tokens: `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`
- Reference: `components/ui/button.tsx` for examples

### Component Patterns
- Follow shadcn/ui architecture
- Use CVA (class-variance-authority) for variants
- Use `cn()` utility from `@/lib/utils`
- Include `forwardRef` and `displayName`
- Follow structure from `components/ui/button.tsx`

### TypeScript
- Use React 19.2.0 types
- Use `VariantProps<typeof componentVariants>`
- Proper prop typing

